news.title: China's new home prices decline 4.8% in February as stimulus efforts fall flat
news.para: The decline of 0.1% versus a month earlier came after two months of relatively steady prices, showed Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics data.

news.title: Property investment in China falls 9.8% in Jan-Feb 2025
news.para: Property sales by floor area dropped 5.1% from a year earlier, compared with a 12.9% decline last year.

news.title: House prices in New Zealand rise in February on growing buyer interest: REINZ
news.para: Seasonally adjusted median house prices nudged 1.7% higher from January, though they were down 0.6% from a year earlier, REINZ data showed.

news.title: Kerala: Cial director board approves phase II rehabilitation plan
news.para: Previous rehabilitation package included job opportunities for displaced people in Cial and other related institutions based on educational qualifications, priority in allotting taxi permits and membership in headload workers' society.

news.title: State government to release final Coimbatore masterplan in May 2025
news.para: The draft masterplan for Coimbatore was released in February 2024. "After perusing all the suggestions, important suggestions will be added, and some changes will be made in the draft masterplan.

news.title: Jaipur: JDA’s expansion plans under master plan 2047 attract criticism
news.para: Chandra Sekhar Parashar, a retired additional chief town planner of Rajasthan, said JDA officials have not undertaken any scientific study to propose the extension of territory.

news.title: Kochi metro likely to miss deadline for phase II works
news.para: This is not due to lack of funding. Beijing-based Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank (AIIB) has granted financial assistance for Phase II line.

news.title: E-khata mandate slows property deals in Karnataka, revenue shortfall looms
news.para: The remaining 29 districts contributed over Rs 5,000 crore, but with just weeks left for the end of the fiscal, authorities are scrambling to boost revenue inflow to meet the target.

news.title: Companies go asset-light, put IT campuses on the block
news.para: India's companies are increasingly selling large IT campuses to optimize operational efficiency and embrace asset-light business models. Firms like Cognizant, Wipro, and DXC Technology have divested expansive properties, capitalizing on changing workforce trends and the rise of remote work, thus reducing real estate expenditures.

news.title: Government to regularise 87 illegal colonies in Jaipur, issue land leases
news.para: These colonies, most of them situated in Sanganer Assembly constituency of Chief Minister Bhajan Lal Sharma, have been encroached upon for years.

news.title: Property owners in Bengaluru to face 100% fine on tax dues from April 1
news.para: BBMP's special commissioner for revenue, Munish Moudgil emphasised that the 2024-25 financial year is set to conclude by the end of this month, and officials must take necessary measures to collect the outstanding property tax without delay.

news.title: Mumbai: Residents of Motilal Nagar await redevelopment with mixed feelings
news.para: The massive 143-acre township comprising 3,700 homes will be redeveloped by Adani group under a Rs 36,000 crore project to be overseen by landowner Mhada. This will be one of the largest Mhada land parcels to undergo redevelopment.

news.title: Blackstone Group strengthens India strategy with foray into housing property market
news.para: Blackstone Group is entering India’s housing market after dominating the commercial property space. Their Rs 1,800 crore commitment involves acquiring a 66% stake in Kolte Patil Developers, focusing on mid-income and premium segments in key cities like Pune, Mumbai, and Bengaluru, leveraging Kolte Patil’s expertise.

news.title: Mumbai EOW registers Rs 750 crore 'fraud' case against Edelweiss
news.para: The case was filed by Ecstasy Realty Pvt Ltd at Amboli police station last month based on a complaint alleging collusion and misappropriation of funds, among other charges. The EOW has taken over the probe in the case.

news.title: Goa: GCCI welcomes GIDC’s decision to reserve 30% of small plots for women applicants
news.para: Twenty industrial plots now have been earmarked for women at Pissurlem, Kundaim, Panchawadi, Madkaim, Verna, Honda and Tuem with plot sizes between 600 and 3,000sqm with a base rate between Rs 1,070 per sqm to 2,810 per sqm.

news.title: Land registrations in Kochi drop by 32% over a decade: Government data

news.para: A Housing and Urban Development Corporation (HUDCO) board meeting held in Mumbai on January 22 had given a green signal for the loan.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh: BOCW approves annual budget of Rs 219.46 crore for FY26
